<HEADLINE> Uganda Praised for Local Governance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Uganda has been ranked among
the countries which have represented the best political and
economic conditions through the local government system, Radio
Uganda reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Research in Africa has proven that Uganda has made a lot of
progress in governance, Bart Halffen, director of studies in the
Institute of Social Studies in the Hague of the Netherlands, said
in a speech presented at a regional seminar on decentralization in
Jinja, 80 km east of the capital city Kampala Monday.
</P>
<P>
However, Halffen warned decentralized organs against relying on
the central government for funding.
</P>
<P>
The scholar also advocated the need for the non-governmental
organizations and the private sector to participate in the making
of decentralization policies.
</P>
<P>
The five-day seminar has drawn scholars from eastern and
southern African countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
