<HEADLINE> World Bank to Provide $114M for Uganda's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 6 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank has approved a
114- million-U.S. dollar fund for the local government development
program and the second economic and financial management project
in Uganda.
</P>
<P>
Some 18 million dollars would be used to support the government
 development strategies contained in the country's Poverty
Eradication Action Plan 1997, Radio Uganda reported on Monday
evening.
</P>
<P>
The second economic and financial project is aimed to improve
the effectiveness of public expenditure management including
government planning, financial management, monitoring and
evaluation.
</P>
<P>
Both projects were jointly funded by the Ugandan government,
Kampala City Council and local governments, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank and the International Monetary Fund (IMF) are
the key multilateral financial institutions which provide colossal
amount of money for the east African country's economic
development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
