<HEADLINE> Cyprus Airways Y2K Compliant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus Airways (CY), the
country's national carrier, said Monday that it is completely Y2K
compliant and ready both in air and on the ground to handle the
computer bug, a statement of the airline said.
</P>
<P>
The airways has successfully conducted a simulation flight in
Y2K conditions. Thirty minutes into the flight, when the clock of
a no-passenger Airbus A-320 struck the millennium switchover, its
computer systems were adjusted in tandem.
</P>
<P>
The three pilots flew the aircraft for further two hours, with
all systems responding without any problems. The plane returned
safely to airport around midday, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
"With today's flight, Cyprus Airways has confirmed assurances
by manufacturer Airbus Industries of the Y2K compatibility of its
aircraft."
</P>
<P>
Around 700 electronic systems on the ground have been tested,
some were replaced and others repaired and are now completely Y2K
compatible.
</P>
<P>
The International Air Transport Association (IATA) has placed
Cyprus Airways in the list of airlines which are not expected to
face any problems during the switchover to the year 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
