<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Third Chernobyl Reactor Restored </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 6 (Xinhua) -- The third power unit of the
Chernobyl nuclear power station using an RMBK-1000 reactor was
switched on again to the Ukrainian power grid Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The unit was turned on after a piping defect was removed, the
Interfax news agency quoted the nuclear plant's press service as
saying Monday.
</P>
<P>
On Monday morning, both turbo generators of the reactor started
to operate. The capacity of the unit was raised to 75 percent of
the nominal level that stands at 1,000 megawatts, and continues to
increase.
</P>
<P>
The reactor was shut down due to a failure of piping and cut
off from the power circuit, which was discovered during a routine
examination of equipment on the evening of December 1.
</P>
<P>
However, the press center of the Chernobyl nuclear power plant
asserted that the radiation background in the territory of the
reactor was below normal level and no safety regulations were
broken.
</P>
<P>
The third reactor of the Chernobyl station was switched on on
November 26 after a prolonged planned repair that began on July 1
this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
