<HEADLINE> Voting Support Helicopter Crashes in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, November 6 (Xinhua) -- A helicopter carrying 20 members
of polling station staff and kits of voting materials crashed
Monday on take- off in the Luabo administrative post in
Mozambique's central province of Zambezia, an election official
confirmed.
</P>
<P>
The two crew members and some of the passengers were slightly
injured, but the electoral materials are said to have suffered no
damage, said Adolfo Gomes, Director of the provincial branch of
the Electoral Administration Technical Secretariat.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred when the helicopter broke one of its
rotor blades when it hit a branch of a tree on take-off, Radio
Mozambique quoted Gomes as saying.
</P>
<P>
A local police source said that a rescue team has been
dispatched to the site of the accident. 
</P>
