<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Morocco Gets UNDP Support in Strengthening Court System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, December 6 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) and the Government of Morocco have
launched a five-year program to strengthen the Moroccan Supreme
Court, UNDP officials said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The initiative will improve and modernize the national
judiciary system by supporting capacity-building and providing
training for magistrates, clerks and technical staff, the
officials said.
</P>
<P>
It will also help establish a new information management
scheme and a modern judiciary documentation system, said the
officials.
</P>
<P>
The 4.4-million U.S. dollar project, financed largely by the
Supreme Court and by a 200,000-U.S. dollar contribution from UNDP,
is the seventh sub-program of the Morocco and UNDP Rabat Framework
for Good Governance and Institutional Reinforcement.
</P>
<P>
UNDP, set up in 1965, is the world's largest multilateral
source of grants for sustainable human development. The U.N.
agency coordinates most of the technical assistance provided by
the U.N. system.  
</P>
</TEXT>
