<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Sets Condition for Accepting OAU Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Prime Minister
Meles Zenawi said here Monday that his country will not accept the
technical arrangement for an end to the Ethio-Eritrean conflict
unless the document was prepared to guarantee its sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
The technical arrangement was drafted by some parties who were
not part of the Organization of African Unity (OAU) framework
agreement from the start, Meles told Ethiopian TV, noting the
document has failed to ensure the sovereignty of Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
Saying the technical arrangement has distorted and revised the
peace proposals, Meles stressed that only the African heads of
state and government have the mandate to change the peace
proposals endorsed at the consecutive OAU summits in Ouagadougou
and Algiers.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia could say the technical arrangement has become in line
with the OAU peace package if only it ensured the return of the
previous Ethiopian civilian administration with all its
structures, Meles said.
</P>
<P>
War broke out between Ethiopia and Eritrea in early May last
year over a disputed patch of border land, causing tens of
thousands of deaths and numerous injuries to both sides. 
</P>
</TEXT>
