<HEADLINE> London - A Leading Center For International Legal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 6 (Xinhua) - London is a leading center for
international legal services, according to a report launched
Monday by British Invisibles (BI).
</P>
<P>
Out of the largest 50 firms in the world there are more based
in London than any other center - 10, compared with 9 in New York,
5 in Chicago and 4 in Los Angeles and San Francisco.
</P>
<P>
While a core expertise in English law has been pivotal to the
success of City law firms some have also developed a capability in
New York state law to enable firms to offer a broader service to
their clients, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The increasing business in financial markets has helped to
drive growth in fee income, with law firms' overseas earnings
rising to 790 million pounds in 1998, an increase of more than 50
percent from 511 million pounds in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the launching of the report, Jeremy Seddon, chief
executive of BI said: "The leading position of City law firms
reflects the dominant position of London as an international
financial center and, in particular, the growth of business
generated by investment banks."
</P>
<P>
"City law firms have applied a wide range of business
management disciplines to the conduct of their practice, for
example embracing technology to a much greater extent than is
typical in law firms elsewhere," he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
