<HEADLINE> UK's Manufacturing Sector Continues To Recover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 6 (Xinhua) -- The UK's manufacturing sector is
continuing to recover from the past year's lows, according to the
latest figures released Monday.
</P>
<P>
Industrial production rose 0.2 percent in October, but was up
by a more robust 1.5 percent on the year, the Office for National
Statistics (ONS) said.
</P>
<P>
Manufacturing saw a 1.3 percent improvement on the year, the
strongest rise for two years. The three-monthly figures pointed to
a rise of 1 percent for the sector and for industrial production
as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Economists said despite the persistent strength of the pound
this was the best performance for nearly 18 months.
</P>
<P>
The Bank of England's Monetary Policy Committee is due to
announce its decision on interest rates this week, with a majority
of economists expecting no change in the current level of 5.5
percent.
</P>
<P>
However, observers here believe that the latest figures put
some pressure on the MPC to raise interest rates this month and
take some of the heat out of the economy.
</P>
</TEXT>
