<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tibet's First Dating Service Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Tibet's first dating service
opened this morning, thanks to the efforts of the autonomous
regional women's federation to help lonely singles.
</P>
<P>
A new survey by the federation shows that single men and women
account for some 20 percent of all staff members of government
departments in the autonomous region, most of whom say they are
looking for more ways to find compatible partners.
</P>
<P>
The service has triggered widespread interest and concern from
both young people and the elderly, with more than 100 phone calls
for details logged since August when the news about the service
leaked out.
</P>
<P>
So far, more than 70 percent of the applicants are women, the
majority of which are divorced, an official with the agency said,
without giving the exact number of them.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that in recent years, the divorce rate in Lhasa,
capital of the Tibet Autonomous Region, has been increasing
steadily. Some 490 residents of Lhasa were granted divorces this
year, accounting for 17 percent of the new couples.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
