<HEADLINE> Sensex Up in Bombay Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive Index (SENSEX)
Tuesday rose by 28.64 points on the Bombay Stock Exchange
following hectic buying by Foreign Institutional Investors and
short-coverings by operators.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-30 share sensitive index ended at 4,864.62 as against
Monday's close of 4,835.98, registering a marginal gain of 28.64
