<HEADLINE> Following are highlights of the diplomatic news released today by Xinhua: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China and the European Union (EU) initialed an agreement here
Monday on extending the sixth bilateral agreement on textile
products for one year to December 31, 2000.
</P>
<P>
The two sides initialed the agreement in the form of "
exchanging letters", according to sources with China's Ministry of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
 CPC Delegation Heads for Zimbabwe, Tanzania
</P>
<P>
A delegation of the Communist Party of China left here today
for Zimbabwe and Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
 Chinese Defense Minister Meets New Zealand Guest
</P>
<P>
Chinese Defense Minister Chi Haotian said today that relations
between China and New Zealand have been growing steadily in recent
years.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission and
State Councilor, made the remarks at a meeting with Chief of the
Army Maurice Dodson of New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
Dodson said that New Zealand attaches importance to the
development of relations between the two countries and their armed
forces and that New Zealand is willing to join efforts with China
to contribute to peace, stability and development in the region.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Defense Minister Meets Jordanian Guest
</P>
<P>
Chi Haotian met here today with Mohammad Yussef Al-Malkawi,
chief of general staff of the Jordanian armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Chi said that developing bilateral friendly relations is
conducive to the interests of both countries, and that the
development of friendly ties between the armed forces of the two
countries will further promote exchanges and cooperation in many
fields.
</P>
