<HEADLINE> S. African Post Office Well-Prepared for Y2K </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The South African Post
Office confirmed in Pretoria on Tuesday that its systems are
already Y2K compliant.
</P>
<P>
Karl Bailey, Chairman of the Post Office's Y2K steering
committee, said in a statement reaching here that its preparing
work, which began in 1996, has finally been completed.
</P>
<P>
"We have made preparations for the new millennium within budget
and we are confident there would be no hitches," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said Y2K regional and national operation centres have been
established to co-ordinate and monitor activities during the
century change- over. 
