<HEADLINE> Northwest Airlines Cooperates with Chinese Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Northwest Airlines from the
United States today signed a contract with Shanghai Pudong
Development Bank to extend loans for Chinese people studying
abroad.
</P>
<P>
The bank and Northwest have jointly made a service plan for
loan applicants, under which people who apply to the bank for
study abroad in 2000 will get favorable air ticket prices to the
United States, Europe, and Japan, and will become a member of the
World Perks Mileage Program with no charge.
</P>
<P>
Pudong Development Bank and Northwest Airlines will hold
contests for students to get free air tickets provided by
Northwest and KLM Royal Dutch Airlines.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Pudong Development Bank has promoted the loans for
Chinese people studying abroad since this July. To date, there
have been over 60 successful applicants, with a total amount in
loans at over seven million yuan. 
</P>
