<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Plane With 17 Aboard Goes Missing in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Asian Spirit plane, with 15 passengers and two crew members
on board, took off from Manila at 08:34 (00:34 GMT) and was
scheduled to arrive at the northern town of Cauayan, Isabela
Province, at 09:40 (01:40 GMT), the officials said.
</P>
<P>
Airports along the route were being contacted to check if the
twin-engine plane had landed anywhere else, but there was no such
word yet, said Rolando Luna, executive director of the Air
Transportation Office.
</P>
<P>
He said that aviation officials in Manila have been
coordinating with their counterparts in the north, and an air
force helicopter has been dispatched from Cauayan to conduct a
search mission. 
</P>
