<DOCNO> XIE19991207.0079 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-07 14:44 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Albright in Damascus for Peace Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, December 7 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright arrived here from Saudi Arabia Tuesday
afternoon for a one-day visit to Syria.
</P>
<P>
She was welcomed at the Damascus International Airport by her
Syrian counterpart Farouq al-Sharaa.
</P>
<P>
The visit was aimed at reviving the Syrian-Israeli peace talks
which have been stalled since February 1996 and making further
progress in the implementation of the Sharm el Sheikh memorandum
signed in September by the Palestinians and Israel.
</P>
<P>
Albright is to hold talks with Syrian President Hafez al-Assad
and Sharaa on the Middle East peace process soon after her arrival.
</P>
<P>
Observers here said that Albright's ongoing multi-leg regional
tour which has taken her to Saudi Arabia, highlighted anew the
crucial U.S. role in the peace process in the Middle East with
special attention attached to the Syrian-Israeli track.
</P>
<P>
On the eve of Albright's Middle East tour, which will also take
her to Israel, Palestinian territories and Egypt, Washington
renewed its commitment to a comprehensive peace in the region and
pledged full cooperation with the parties concerned towards that
goal.
</P>
<P>
Israel and Syria have expressed willingness to resume peace
negotiations but differ on where to begin with. Assad insisted
that Israel keep its verbal promise to return the Golan Heights it
captured in 1967 from Syria, but Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak
rejected such a precondition.
</P>
<P>
Barak had vowed to try to put an end to the Israeli-Arab
conflicts. Efforts were being made to conclude a final peace
agreement with the Palestinians while seeking a resumption of
peace talks with Syria and Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a meeting of the Engineer Syndicate Assembly in
Syria on Monday, Assistant Secretary General of the ruling Ba'ath
party Solieman Kadah expressed welcome to all international
efforts and initiatives to revive the peace talks on the
Syrian-Israeli track. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
