<HEADLINE> Assad Meets U.S. Secretary of State on Mideast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Syrian President Hafez
al-Assad Tuesday afternoon met visiting U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright on the Syrian-Israeli peace talks.
</P>
<P>
Syrian Foreign Minister Farouq al-Sharaa, U.S. Assistant
Secretary of State Martin Indyk, U.S. Mideast Peace Coordinator
Dennis Ross were also present at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Albright, who started her Mideast tour Monday, arrived here
earlier in the day on a one-day visit. She has visited Saudi
Arabia and will also visit Israel and Palestinian self-rule areas
with an aim of giving the Middle East peace process a push.
</P>
<P>
The eighth session of the Palestinian-Israeli talks for a
permanent peace ended inconclusively Monday, with the Palestinian
side refusing further negotiations with Israel if it continues the
settlements expansion.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the peace talks on the Syrian-Israeli and
Lebanese-Israeli tracks are still bogged down in impasse. 
