<HEADLINE> Thai Government OKs Thai Airways' Plane Purchase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The Thai cabinet on Tuesday
approved a finance ministry proposal for state-run Thai Airways
International to tap local and foreign loans to finance aircraft
purchases, according to a Government House press release.
</P>
<P>
The government agreed to let Thai Airways take out up to 10.5
billion baht (261.3 million U.S. dollars) of local long-term loans
to finance its previously-announced purchase of an Airbus 330-300
and a Boeing 747-400.
</P>
<P>
The airline will also seek about 5.76 billion dollars foreign
loans to purchase another Boeing 747-400 and four Boeing 777-300.
</P>
<P>
The Barclays Asia Limited was designated as loan seeker while
the Export and Import Bank of the United States and Export Credits
Guaranty Department from Britain will be the loan guarantors.
</P>
