<HEADLINE> Iran Operates Anti-Tank Missile Production Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Minister of Defense and
the Armed Forces Logistics Admiral Ali Shamkhani on Tuesday
inaugurated a production line for Tousan (Mustang) 1 anti-tank
missile.
</P>
<P>
Shamkhani said the Iranian defensive industries are now
capable of producing fundamental hardwares needed in the country,
the Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Ahmad Vahid, director of the Iranian Aerospace Organization
that is responsible for the production line, said that the range
of the Tousan 1 missile is four kilometers in the day and 2.5
kilometers at night if it is equipped with night-vision binoculars.
</P>
<P>
Vahid said that the missile can be fired from personnel
carriers or from the ground. But he did not give the capacity of
the production line. 
