<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wei Jianxing on Reform and Stability of Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 7 (Xinhua) -- All enterprises should promote
development, reform and stability by deepening the system of equal
consultation and collective contracts, a top Chinese trade union
official said today.
</P>
<P>
Wei Jianxing, president of the All-China Federation of Trade
Unions and member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee, made the
remarks during an inspection of the Beijing Jeep Co. Ltd this
morning.
</P>
<P>
He said that an effective system of adjusting labor relations
according to law should be established in enterprises and issues
concerning payment, labor security, hygienic conditions, insurance
and welfare of employees should be discussed equally among
employees and trade unions.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that all the enterprises should introduce the
collective contract system, which can play an important role in
protecting employees' benefits.
</P>
<P>
Experience from the Beijing Jeep Co. Ltd and other companies in
Beijing has proved that the system is beneficial for promoting the
reform, development and stability of enterprises, Wei concluded.
</P>
</TEXT>
