each other in many areas.
</P>
<P>
Especially in bilateral economic cooperation there are great
potential and broad prospects, he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that the king has contributed a lot to the growth of
Sino-Jordanian relations and the current visit will further
promote the friendly ties.
</P>
<P>
King Abdullah II told Zhu that his present China tour has been
a success and achieved the expected goal.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that China values its ties with Jordan, and bilateral
relations in politics, economy, culture and other fields have had
sound development since the two forged diplomatic ties 22 years
ago.
</P>
<P>
China and Jordan have supported each other in international
affairs through effective coordination and cooperation, he said,
adding that China appreciates the "one China" position adhered by
Jordan and is confident that Jordan will continue to support China
's reunification cause.
</P>
<P>
The king said that Jordan and China have close ties and
bilateral cooperation in political and other fields is
satisfactory. He cited China's important contribution to the
Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
He said that he would continue to stick to the "one China"
policy.
</P>
<P>
The king said he is optimistic about the prospects of Jordan-
China economic cooperation, hoping that the economic cooperation
between China and the Middle East countries would be further
enhanced.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed the hope that the Jordan-China relations
would serve as a model for ties between Asian and Middle East
countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
