<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> England to Meet Germany in 2002 World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Arch rivals England and Germany
will have to battle each other for the one automatic qualifying
spot from the same group as the draw was made on Tuesday for the
qualifying competition of the 2002 World Cup.
</P>
<P>
Ironically the two nationals are also the rivals to win the bid
to stage the 2006 World Cup.
</P>
<P>
England, which failed to be listed among the top seeds for the
nine European groups, was dramatically drew with Germany in group
nine, which also featured Greece, Finland and Albania.
</P>
<P>
Germany, a three-time champion, and England, which beat Germany
for its only title when it hosted the 1966 World Cup, have had a
long history at major championships.
</P>
<P>
In their last championship match, Germany beat England in the
semi-finals of the 1996 European Championships, before going on to
win the title.
</P>
<P>
Italy, another traditional powerhouse which failed to obtain
top seeding, also faced a daunting task as they were paired with
Romania, Lithuania, Hungary and Georgia.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands, a perennial World Cup favorite but never a
champion, also got a tough draw after they are placed in a six-
team group with Portugal, the Republic of Ireland, Cyprus, Andorra
and Estonia.
</P>
<P>
In aother tough European group Euro 2000 finalists Yugoslavia
and Slovenia were drawn with Russia and Switzerland in group one.
</P>
<P>
Only groups winners qualify directly for the finals to be
played June 1-30, 2002.
</P>
<P>
Eight runners-up will go into playoff to determine four more
finalists, while another runner-up will face an Asian team for the
last place that could go to Europe.
</P>
<P>
The draw in a modernistic, ship-shaped Tokyo exhibition hall
started the countdown to the first World Cup to be shared by two
hosts, Japan and South Korea.
</P>
<P>
A record 195 nations and regions took part in the draw, while
defending champions France and the two hosts Japan and South Korea
qualify directly.
</P>
<P>
The qualifying process, which begins in March and involves
hundreds of matches, will eventually produce 29 other finalists.
</P>
</TEXT>
