<HEADLINE> Recognition of Bangla by UNESCO Celebrated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, November 7 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of thousands of
Bangladeshi joined a grand rally here Tuesday to celebrate the
recognition of February 21 as the International Mother Language
Day by the United Nations Education Scientific and Cultural
Organization (UNESCO).
</P>
<P>
Addressing the rally, Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina said, " it
is the Bengalis who have taught the world how to give blood to
protect the mother tongue."
</P>
<P>
The prime minister announced that an international research
center will be set up in Dhaka to protect and promote the nearly 6,
000 languages of the world.
</P>
<P>
"We will set up the research center where the specimen of all
the mother languages will be preserved for their protection and
promotion," she said.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Hasina noted that the decision of UNESCO was "a world
recognition to Bangla and the Bengali nation's struggle for
rights."
</P>
<P>
UNESCO recognized February 21 as the International Mother
Language Day on November 16. A total of 188 member countries of
UNESCO unanimously decided to observe February 21 as the
International Mother Language Day across the globe. 
</P>
