<HEADLINE> China to Promote Education in Accordance with Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 7 (Xinhua) -- China will take measures to
promote education in accordance with law, and provide a strong
legal guarantee for maintaining priority status for education, a
top education official said today.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Kaixuan, chairman of the Education, Science, Culture and
Public Health Committee of the National People Congress, was
speaking at the national conference on the legal work in education,
which opened today.
</P>
<P>
The conference, co-sponsored by the NPC Education, Science,
Culture and Public Health Committee and the Ministry of Education,
is the first of its kind held since the People's Republic of China
was founded in 1949.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that the Chinese government has paid great attention
to the legal construction in education. Since 1980, the NPC and
the NPC standing committee have issued 16 education regulations
and laws including the Education Law, the Compulsory Education Law,
and the Higher Education Law, all of which have largely promoted
China's education reform and development.
</P>
<P>
However, there is still much work to do, said Zhu, such as
supplementing and amending the present educational law system and
promoting educational law.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Education Chen Zhili said that the CPC central
committee and the State Council have taken a series of steps to
deepen education reform and development this year. Education
departments should promote and guarantee education reform through
legal channels, Chen said.
</P>
<P>
Chen also pointed out that education departments at all levels
should protect youth and students' legal rights, cooperate with
other departments to establish a comprehensive enforcement system,
and provide legal direction and assistance to middle and primary
schools. 
</P>
</TEXT>
