<HEADLINE> Gold, Silver Up in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Prices of gold and silver
recovered smartly on the bullion market Tuesday in Mumbai (Bombay)
following better overseas advices coupled with thin supply.
</P>
<P>
Standard gold ended at 4,400 rupees (102.32 U.S. dollars) per
10 grams, showing a rise of 20 rupees (0.46 dollar) from the last
close of 4,380 rupees (101.86 dollars).
</P>
