rupees (94.65 dollars) per 10 grams from Monday's mark of 4,050
rupees (94.19 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, ready silver (.999 fineness) closed at 8,055 rupees
(187.32 dollars) per kilogram, showing a good gain of 75 rupees (1.
74 dollars) over the previous close of 7,980 rupees (185.58
dollars).
</P>
<P>
However, raw silver (.916 fineness) shot up by 115 rupees (2.67
dollars) to 7,960 rupees (185.12 dollars) from Monday's close of 7,
845 rupees (182.45 dollars) per kg. 
