<HEADLINE> Russia's GDP to Hit 207.4 Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Russia's gross domestic product
(GDP) will reach 5.6 trillion rubles (207.4 billion U.S. dollars)
next year, higher than the 5.35 trillion rubles (198.1 billion
dollars) predicted by the draft budget, a senior Russian financial
official said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference, Russian First Deputy Finance Minister
Aleksei Kudrin said Russia's GDP is expected to grow 1.6 percent
this year and even more next year.
</P>
<P>
"These indicators will be adjusted in the budget, which will
increase budget revenue," Kudrin said.
</P>
<P>
Budget revenue in November this year was 60 billion rubles (2.2
billion dollars), while the planned monthly figure for next year
is 66 billion rubles (2.4 billion dollars), he said.
</P>
<P>
Kudrin said the budget passed recently by the State Duma (lower
house of the Russian parliament) is realistic and can be
implemented. 
