<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Transport Ready to Meet 2YK Compliance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding rail transport, Omar said, all the signalling control
systems of the South African Rail Commuter Corporation are
well-equipped, with the power supply to most of the operational
control centres doubled up and Y2K compliant.
</P>
<P>
The major fuel stations along all national roads would be in a
position to supply fuel and the Department of Mineral and Energy
Affairs has given the assurance that there will be no problems, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Commending on concerns of the functioning of traffic lights and
traffic management systems, Omar said these are under the direct
control of the provincial and local governments. 
