<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 500,000 African Women Die of Child Birth Annually </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 7 (Xinhua) -- At least 500,000 African women
died of child birth every year, a Zambian government official
said.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Health Minister Enerst Mwansa told the African Midwives
Research Network meeting that the maternal mortality rate stands
at 649 to 800 per 100,000 live births in Zambia.
</P>
<P>
He said in his country's rural areas, most of those who survive
child birth suffer permanent disabilities.
</P>
<P>
"In order to help reduce maternal mortality in African
countries, there is need for midwives to carry out operational
research and effectively utilize the findings," he said.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania, Zimbabwe, Zambia, Mozambique and Sweden are
represented at the meeting. 
</P>
