<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rally on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Share prices rallied to close
sharply higher on Singapore Stock Market Tuesday, pushing the key
indicator to a new record high.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Time Index (STI) soared 56.03 points, or
2.5 percent, to end at 2,299.87 points.
</P>
<P>
The volume totaled 280 million units valued at 640.7 million
Singapore dollars (381.37 million U.S. dollars). Gainers led
losers by 244 to 69 with 158 stocks staying unchanged.
</P>
<P>
MfgIntegTec continued to lead the volume list with 35.1 million
shares transacted at 0.715 Singapore dollars per share. It was
followed by AFP which had a volume of 31.61 million stocks. PCI A
was the next with 17 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 was the biggest gainer of the day surging up 200
cents to a close of 28.5 Singapore dollars. SPH ran up 190 cents
to finish at 34.9 Singapore dollars. SPH climbed up by 180 cents
to end at 34.9 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Gr Eastern led losers of the day incurring a
loss of 20 cents to close at 17.9 Singapore dollars. Labroy sank
17 cents to finish at 1.63 Singapore dollars. JurShip retreated 15
cents to end at 8.05 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the market's advance was led by electronics and
banking sector stocks.
</P>
<P>
They added that technology stocks were boosted by Nasdaq's
record close on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
