<HEADLINE> Gold Price in Hong Kong Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The gold price in Hong Kong
went up three HK dollars to close at 2,586 dollars a tael today,
according to Po Sang Bank, one of the major gold dealers in Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
The gold price is equivalent to 279.26 U.S. dollars a troy
ounce, 0.35 U.S. dollars down from the previous close, at Tuesday'
s exchange rate of one U.S. dollar against 7.7730 HK dollars.
</P>
