<HEADLINE> Australia Stocks Closes Weaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 7 (Xinhua) -- the Australian stock market
Tuesday closed weaker with the benchmark all ordinaries index
finished the day down 27.4 points at 3,105.9, reversing much of
Monday's strong gains.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index fell 48.7 points to 5,399.7 and the
all resources index closed 9.9 points lower at 1,298.8.
</P>
<P>
Profit-takers moved out of News Corp with the global media
giant's shares falling 61 cents to 9.59 U.S. dollars after hitting
a record close of 9.91 U.S. dollars Monday.
</P>
<P>
Telecommunications company Optus shares, which soared Monday to
an all-time high of 3.08 U.S. dollars, easing eight cents to 3.03
U.S.dollars. Telstra lost four cents to 5.65 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
National Australia Bank fell 24 cents to 14.41 U.S. dollars and
Commonwealth Bank was down nine cents to 16.29 U.S. dollars, but
ANZ bank finished steady at 7.24 U.S. dollars and Westpac bank
gained six cents to 6.8 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Challenged by a new rival Virgin, the airlines Qantas fell 12
cents to 2.46 U.S. dollars. Virgin Airlines Tuesday afternoon
cleared the first hurdle in its attempt to establish a third
domestic airline in Australia when it was granted foreign
investment approval by the Australian government.
</P>
<P>
Resources giant BHP finished 20 cents lower at 11.3 U.S.
dollars and Rio Tinto was down 32.1 to 18.03 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover reached 829.69 million shares valued at 118.
69 million U.S. dollars with 844 falls, 580 rises and 499 stocks
steady. 
</P>
</TEXT>
