<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK's Latest Foreign Currency Assets Figures Released </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The official foreign currency
assets of Hong Kong amounted to 92.1 billion U.S. dollars at the
end of November 1999, the Hong Kong Monetary Authority (HKMA)
announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Including unsettled forward contracts, the foreign currency
assets of Hong Kong at the end of November 1999 stood at 92.6
billion U.S. dollars, compared with 90.4 billion U.S. dollars at
the end of October.
</P>
<P>
According to an HKMA spokesperson, the 1.7-billion-U.S.-dollar
increase in settled foreign currency assets during the month
reflects mainly the conversion into U.S. dollars as part of the
proceeds from the sale of Hong Kong equities through the Tracker
Fund.
</P>
<P>
In terms of foreign currency reserves ranking, Hong Kong is the
world's fifth largest holder of foreign currency reserves after
Japan, the Chinese Mainland, Taiwan and Germany.
</P>
<P>
The total foreign currency assets of 92.1 billion U.S. dollars
represent over seven times the currency in circulation or about 38
percent of Hong Kong dollar M3, one of the highest ratios in the
world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
