<DOCNO> XIE19991207.0169 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya's Food Policy Fails to Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Kenya's national food policy
adopted in 1994 has failed to achieve its objectives, Kenya's
Agriculture Minister Chris Obure was quoted by Tuesday's Daily
Nation newspaper as saying.
</P>
<P>
Obure said that the policy including the abolishment of price
fixing, the removal of the monopoly and the freeing up of grain
movement was meant to boost food production in a liberalized
market.
</P>
<P>
Although the government had effected a duty waiver for
fertilizers to encourage food production, the commodity was still
expensive, he told a seminar.
</P>
<P>
Obure said the food policy should be reviewed to ensure food
security, citing that the output of major staple foods had been
overtaken by consumption.
</P>
<P>
Maize production is 30 million bags against a consumption of 33
million bags and wheat three million bags against seven million,
according to Obure.
</P>
<P>
Whereas the country had an irrigation potential of more than
400,000 hectares, only 30,000 are under irrigation, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991207.0170 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Reports Rapid Industrial Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 7 (Xinhua) -- China had 7.6 percent growth in
its industrial added value output in November, according to the
National Statistics Bureau,
</P>
<P>
The country's industrial added value output totaled 191.9
billion yuan for the period and 1817.7 billion yuan from January
to November, up 9 percent from the same last year period.
</P>
<P>
In November, the incremental output value in the state sector
was up 6.5 percent. In collectively-owned firms it was up 4.9
percent and in overseas-funded companies it was up 14.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
In November, light industry had 83.4 billion yuan in output
value, up 7.4 percent from the same period last year, while heavy
industry was up 7.8 percent to 108.5 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
November witnessed rapid output growth of steel, textile
products, some durable consumer products and telecommunications
products. November also witnessed a higher sales ratio for
industrial products, with 97.28 percent of production being sold,
up 0.54 percent from November last year, while industrial exports
increased 13.7 percent, up 4.3 percent from October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
