<HEADLINE> ROK Companies Enter China Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Recovering from an economic
recession, companies from the Republic of Korea (ROK) are making a
comeback on the Chinese market amply illustrated at a Product and
Technology Expo in the northern port city of Tianjin during
December 1-4. Eighty four companies from ROK attended the expo.
</P>
<P>
The companies deal in electronics information, environmental
protection, machinery, automatic control, appliances and meters,
household electric appliances, light industry, as well as textiles,
bio-medicine and food processing.
</P>
<P>
An official at ROK's Small and Medium Industry Promotion Corp.
Cho Jung Kun, said he was surprised to see so many companies,
considering the fact that ROK has been through an economic
recession.
</P>
<P>
Cho, who is in charge of the company's Beijing branch, said the
overwhelming presence of ROK companies at the expo is an obvious
sign of a growing interest in the Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
The ROK government set up the Small and Medium Industry
Promotion Corporation in 1993 to promote ROK's medium-sized and
small enterprises in China.
</P>
<P>
Before the expo, China and ROK signed an agreement promoting
such enterprises. Under the agreement, agencies set up by the ROK
government in China will provide consulting services, technical
support and personnel training.
</P>
<P>
The Small and Medium Industry Promotion Corporation plans to
set up a second branch in China's largest industrial and
commercial center, Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Officials at the ROK embassy in China said that the ROK
government will set up an agency to help ROK firms evaluate
investment risks and find business opportunities in China.
</P>
<P>
In Tianjin, ROK has set up 1,015 companies with contractual
investment valued at 1.9 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
China and ROK signed 4,500 agreements on developing medium-
sized and small companies in March this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
