<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Several Kenyan companies will
be listed on the Johannesburg Stock Exchange, South Africa, early
next year, Chairman of the Nairobi Stock Exchange Jimnah Mbaru has
said.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the top managers of the listed companies here
Monday, Mbaru said there are plans to have several blue-chip
Kenyan firms listed on the Johannesburg stock market, the East
African Standard newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Mbaru named Kenya Airways, East African Breweries and the Kenya
 Commercial Bank as some of the highly rated Kenyan firms that
might benefit from the cross-border listing.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that Castle Breweries and Old Mutual (SA) are
among some of the South African blue-chip companies to be listed
on the Nairobi exchange.
</P>
<P>
Mbaru described cross-border listing as a way forward for
Africa's emerging market, saying plans are underway to harmonize
the listing requirements for the 20 stock markets in Africa.
</P>
