<HEADLINE> China to Use "Green" Power-generating Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The Yantai Power Plant in the
coastal city of Yantai in Shandong Province is preparing for the
introduction of an environment-friendly electricity-generating
technology on an experimental basis, to turn itself into a "green"
power-generating facility.
</P>
<P>
The power plant is set to introduce integrated gasified
combined circulation (IGCC) technology, which will be widely used
in coal-burning thermal power plants in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
There are now more than 20 IGCC power plants built or under
construction worldwide.
</P>
<P>
The new technology will lift coal's heat efficiency by 10
percent and the rate of the coal's desulphurization to more than
99 percent, producing much less coal ash, or none at all. 
</P>
</TEXT>
