<HEADLINE> 14 Killed in Road Accidents in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Fourteen people were killed and
50 others seriously injured in separate road accidents in Kenya
over last weekend.
</P>
<P>
In one accident last Sunday night, seven people died and 11
others seriously injured when a bus collided head-on with a tanker
in an attempt to overtake.
</P>
<P>
Two people were killed in another accident when a rear tyre of
a bus burst and the driver lost control of the vehicle.
</P>
<P>
The drivers of Kenya's privately-owned buses are notorious for
their reckless driving, which has caused frequent accidents in the
east African country. 
</P>
