<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Intensify Economic Diplomacy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 7 (Xinhua)-- The Indonesian government would
intensify its economic diplomacy in a bid to support the country's
ongoing economic recovery program, an official said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"We will intensify our economic diplomacy through political
approaches without ignoring the importance for keeping the
stability of security," Minister of Foreign Affairs Alwi Sihab
said at the parliament.
</P>
<P>
In this case, Indonesia would give priority to countries in the
Middle East, East Europe, South Africa, Asia and Latin America,
the minister said.
</P>
<P>
"The Ministry of Foreign Affairs would like to focus this
economic) diplomacy on the four main sectors as trade, investment,
tourism and services," Sihab added.
</P>
<P>
He also said the development of the services sector could
strengthen the country's bargaining position in the negotiations
of the General Agreement on Trade and Services and the World Trade
Organization in the future.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia would increase its diplomatic efforts through
regional, bilateral and multilateral forums, aiming to reduce and
eradicate the country's trade barriers, both tariff and non-tariff,
he said.
</P>
<P>
"But our priority is how to support the national economic
recovery program. This is the important thing," Sihab said.
</P>
</TEXT>
