<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkish President Warns EU on Turkey's Candidacy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman
Demirel warned Monday that the recent improvement in relations
between Turkey and Greece will be harmed if Ankara is denied
European Union (EU) candidacy at the upcoming EU summit in
Helsinki.
</P>
<P>
Demirel sounded the warning on board his plane en route to
Bosnia-Herzegovina for a two-day official visit, Turkey's
English-language Daily News reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He warned that the thaw in relations between the two neighbors
following two earthquakes in Turkey and one in Greece in the past
four months may be replaced with new tensions if Turkey is denied
candidacy status at the weekend EU summit in the Finnish capital.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is aware of the responsibilities it has to shoulder once
declared an EU candidate, but it will not accept a candidacy
status with strings attached to it, the president said.
</P>
<P>
He said it has become clear that there is a consensus
among all EU members, except Greece, which has not stated a
definite position on the issue, that Turkey should be given
candidacy status.
</P>
<P>
The Greek government now reportedly seems uncertain whether it
should vote in favor of granting Turkey candidacy before
extracting concessions from Ankara on the territorial dispute over
the Aegean waters and the Cyprus issue, two major sources of feud
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
"Our decision will not be voiced until the last moment. It is a
bit premature now to state whether it will be our government's
policy to veto Turkey's bid for EU candidacy. Nothing has been
decided yet," a Greek diplomat in Ankara was quoted in local press
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Softening Turkey's position on the death sentence to Abdullah
Ocalan, captive leader of the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party,
over which EU has expressed strong opposition, Demirel said if
Turkey belongs to Europe, there are European norms and standards
that the country is required to meet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
