<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Mixed in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed mixed in
Tokyo Tuesday, with high-priced information and telecommunications-
related issues dragged down by profit-taking following gains in
early trading.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange surged 86.76 points, or 0.47
percent, from Monday's close to end at 18,593.96.
</P>
<P>
The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all First
Section issues, however, fell 0.66 point or 0.04 percent to 1,632.
14.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section increased to 605.00 million
shares from Monday's 546.24 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Nippon Steel Corp. was the day's most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
Share prices were higher in 16 of the 33 business sectors.
</P>
<P>
The biggest winner was the rubber industry, gaining 2.92
percent, while the electrical machinery sector rose 0.35 percent,
reflecting the gain in the Nasdaq composite index, which hit a
record closing high Monday, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, losers surpassed
gainers 734 to 480, with 132 issues ending unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
