<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Create Ecological Demonstration Area in Inner Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, December 7 (Xinhua) -- China will build an ecological
demonstration area in Hulun Buir League in the Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region in order to strengthen environmental protection
in the area, according to local officials.
</P>
<P>
Known as China's "clean green land," the Hulun Buir League has
a diversity of natural resources including huge grassland areas,
forests, wetlands, and hundreds of rivers and lakes.
</P>
<P>
There are also more than ten national-level nature reserves in
the league including the Hulun Lake Nature Reserve which is home
to 199 species of rare birds.
</P>
<P>
In the forest area of the Greater Hingan Mountain Range there
are also some 3,000 species of birds and 76 varieties of wild
animals, 12 of which are on the top national protection list.
</P>
<P>
But recent years have witnessed worsening ecological conditions
in the area owing to desertification and water pollution, and
local officials said that creating the demonstration area will
contribute to the ecological balance in northern and northeastern
China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
