<HEADLINE> 5 Zambians Die of Food Poisoning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Five people have died of
suspected food poisoning while at least 60 others are battling for
their lives in hospital after they ate bread rolls bought from a
bakery, Zambian press media reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Police spokesman Lemmy Kajoba in Kitwe, Copperbelt Province,
said four members in one family died on Sunday after eating
allegedly poisoned vegetables.
</P>
<P>
Police in the city were investigating the matter to establish
the source of the vegetables and to ascertain whether it was
sprayed.
</P>
<P>
In Lusaka, at least 60 people have been admitted to the
University Teaching Hospital for suspected bread poisoning, and
one of them has died.
</P>
<P>
Lusaka City Council spokesman Daniel M'soka said the bakery had
been closed and its products confiscated. 
</P>
