<HEADLINE> Private Enterprises Report Fast-growing Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Private enterprises in
Zhejiang Province in east China reported a year-on-year 518
percent rise in exports from January to October this year, 487
percentage points higher than the national average.
</P>
<P>
Local private enterprises exported 87 million US dollars worth
of goods during the ten-month period, accounting for 13.8 percent
of the nation's total by private businesses.
</P>
<P>
This huge increase is a result of local efforts to adopt
favorable policies for encouraging the private sector to increase
its presence in overseas markets.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang now has a total of 411 private enterprises with the
right to engage in export business.  
</P>
