<HEADLINE> Symposium on Women Studies in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 7 (Xinhua) -- A symposium on women studies in
the past 50 years sponsored by the All-China Women's Federation (
ACWF), opened in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
Peng Peiyun, president of the ACWF called on all those engaged
in women studies to work hard to research and publish works on
women's liberation with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Peng said that socialist theories on women's liberation should
be a priority for researchers on women studies in China. These
theories must follow the guidance of Marxism and should be aimed
at solving real problems for women in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
More than 240 delegates from 21 provinces, autonomous regions
and municipalities will attend the three-day meeting, which is the
largest gathering on women studies since the founding of new China
in 1949. Participants will discuss a range of topics such as women
in the workplace, the women's movement and other hotly-debated
issues. 
</P>
