<HEADLINE> Suspected Spy Disappears in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 7 (Xinhua) -- One of 11 suspected spies
arrested by Zambian police in August this year has disappeared,
Zambia Daily Mail reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The South African national charged with nine Ukrainians and one
Zambian, was supposed to appear in Lusaka High Court on Monday but
was conspicuously absent with his lawyer, giving no explanation of
his whereabouts.
</P>
<P>
All others involved in the alleged espionage pleaded not guilty
to the charge.
</P>
<P>
The 11 were arrested for allegedly passing over a protected
military place called "PAPA4" at Lusaka International Airport on
August 15 while flying over the airport.
</P>
<P>
The lawyer of the South African national on bail told the high
court that as counsel he did not have any information pertaining
to the whereabouts of him and applied for withdrawal of legal
representation for him.
</P>
<P>
The high court issued a bench warrant against the South
African, a civil aviation consultant with the Ukrainian
government, according to another newspaper The Post. 
</P>
