<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Millennium Bug to Hit Bangladesh's Health Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Millennium Bug to Hit Health Sector of Bangladesh
</P>
<P>
DHAKA, November 7 (Xinhua) -- The cabinet of Bangladesh was
informed Monday night that except for the health sector, the
millennium bug problem would not affect other fields in the
country because of precautionary measures, newspapers here
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
All the major areas adopting high-tech computer technology have
made Y2K compliant 90 or 90 plus percent of their respective
sector, it was told.
</P>
<P>
But the cabinet was further informed that in the health sector
so far 70 percent was made Y2K compliant.
</P>
<P>
The hazards for the remaining 30 percent, specially in case of
medical equipment in the hospitals, might be disastrous.
</P>
<P>
Official sources said the disclosures came as the cabinet held
detailed discussion during a meeting on preparedness to face
apprehended Y2K technological calamity at the dawn of the year
2000.
</P>
<P>
The major sectors in the country related to sophisticated
information technology are financial, energy, telecommunications,
information, transport, industry, medical equipment, health sector
and defense.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the Health Ministry was asked to take
immediate measures to make the medical equipment Y2K compliant to
avert any disaster in the health sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
