<HEADLINE> Seiko-Epson Opens Printer Plant in Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The Seiko-Epson corporation of
Japan is spending 230 million yuan (28 million US dollars) to
launch a plant in Shenzhen in south China's Guangdong Province for
the manufacture of printers.
</P>
<P>
The plant is the Japanese firm's largest printer production
base in the world, and the newly-completed factory, which began
production recently, eventually will be able to turn out some 12
million printers a year.
</P>
<P>
The investors also decided to move the production center for
the jet component, the core part of the printer, to Shenzhen, said
local sources.
</P>
<P>
Seiko-Epson corporation entered the city of Shenzhen in April
1989, and Epson Technologies (Shenzhen) Co. Ltd., Seiko Epson's
invested business in Shenzhen, now has 11,000 employees.
</P>
<P>
Epson Technologies (Shenzhen) Co. Ltd. places high among
overseas-financed businesses in China in terms of annual output
value and export volume, and last year the company generated 2.5
billion yuan (300 million US dollars) in output value. 
</P>
</TEXT>
