<HEADLINE> Government Says Poland Safe From Y2K Problem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, December 7 (Xinhua) -- There will be no chaos during
the coming New Year's Eve in Poland as key social sectors are well
prepared for the Y2K problem, a government official said Monday.
</P>
<P>
There will be no electricity blackout, gas shortage or collapse
of the postal system in Poland when the new millennium arrives,
assured Ignzcy Pardyka, senior information official for Poland's
Ministry of Internal Affairs and Administration.
</P>
<P>
Pardyka said that the power, postal, finance, transportation
and hygiene sectors, and governmental public service agencies are
prepared for the Y2K problem. The Polish government has
established a special task group to deal with the "millennium bug.
"
</P>
<P>
Aviation, railway and sea transportation in Poland will
continue as usual when the year 2000 arrives, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Polish government will double its electricity reserves on
January 1, 2000, and send experts to critical power stations in
case of possible problems, said Polish officials from the Economic
Ministry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
