<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar, Japan Hold Joint Economic Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Myanmar, Japan Hold Joint Economic Conference
</P>
<P>
YANGON, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar and Japan are jointly
holding an economic conference here to promote bilateral economic
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
At the two-day third Myanmar-Japan Joint Economic Conference,
which began Monday, papers on the aftermath of the Asian financial
crisis and on Japan's response to the crisis were presented by
Vice-Governor of the Central Bank of Myanmar U Than Lwin and
Counselor of Mitsui Company Endo respectively.
</P>
<P>
General Secretary of the Myanmar Federation of Chambers of
Commerce and Industry U Zaw Min Win also presented a paper on an
investment analysis of foreign direct investment in Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
In February last year, chambers of commerce and industry of
Myanmar and Japan reached an agreement on the establishment of an
economic cooperation committee between the two sides to enhance
bilateral economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The first and second Myanmar-Japan economic conference were
held in Yangon last year.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, Myanmar has strengthened its economic
cooperation with Japan. In the past five years, Myanmar has
absorbed investment amounting to 123 million U.S. dollars from
Japan in 16 projects, which accounted for 2.18 percent of the
total foreign investment of the 5.6415 billion dollars flowing
into Myanmar during the period.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, bilateral trade was valued at 149.9 million dollars
in the first half of this year, according to official statistics.
</P>
</TEXT>
