<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0800 GMT, December 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON -- The UK's manufacturing sector is continuing to
recover from the past year's lows, according to the latest figures
released Monday.
</P>
<P>
Industrial production rose 0.2 percent in October, but was up
by a more robust 1.5 percent on the year, the Office for National
Statistics (ONS) said. Manufacturing saw a 1.3 percent
improvement on the year, the strongest rise for two years. (UK-
Manufacturing Sector)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
VIENNA -- The average price of OPEC's basket of seven crude
oils dropped slightly to 24.54 U.S. dollars per barrel last week
from 24.90 dollars in the previous week, the secretariat of the
Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) said here
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The average price per barrel in November reached 23.74 dollars,
the highest in recent months, compared with 21.67 dollars in
October. The price averaged only 12.28 dollars per barrel in 1998.
(OPEC-Oil Prices)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Yugoslavia's exports declined by 46.9 percent in
the first 11 months this year while its imports went down by 33.3
percent compared with the same period of last year, the newspaper
Politika reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Exports totaled 1.3 billion U.S. dollars while imports dropped
to 2.9 billion dollars in the period, as a result of the 78-day
airstrikes by the U.S.-led NATO earlier in the year. (Yugoslavia-
Exports)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KAMPALA -- The World Bank has approved a 114- million-U.S.
dollar fund for the local government development program and the
second economic and financial management project in Uganda. (
World Bank-Uganda-Fund) 
</P>
</TEXT>
