<HEADLINE> FIFA Won't Ban Brazil from World Cup, Blatter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 7 (Xinhua) -- FIFA president Joseph Blatter on
Tuesday said that the world soccer body won't ban Brazil from
international competitions for knowingly fielding overage players
in youth competitions.
</P>
<P>
Mexico was given a two-year ban from international soccer in
1988 for similar offenses, forcing them to miss the 1990 World Cup.
</P>
<P>
Blatter said Tuesday that the punishment inflicted on Mexico
had been disproportionate and that any sanctions in future cases
should be confined to the age-level at which the offenses were
committed.
</P>
<P>
"But definitely I can tell you the Brazilian team will not be
suspended for the World Cup whatever will be the outcome of this
investigation," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
