<DOCNO> XIE19991207.0276 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Technology Developed to Burn Garbage to Generate Electricity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese environment protection
experts have made it a point to promote nationwide a technology to
generate electricity through the burning of garbage and waste.
</P>
<P>
The process was developed at Zhejiang University in Hangzhou,
the capital of Zhejiang Province, and is expected to also be used
overseas.
</P>
<P>
A dozen cities in China, including Xi'an, Ningbo, Zhengzhou,
plan to use the process in an effort to dispose of rubbish and
waste at no cost to the environment.
</P>
<P>
The common practice of burying waste has proved harmful to the
environment.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 million tons of rubbish and waste are produced in
urban areas in China every day. The Chinese government has been
urging to adopt favorable policies on pollution-free treatment of
rubbish and waste. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
