<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bucks, Glenn Agrees to Contract Extension </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 6 (Xinhua) -- The Milwaukee Bucks and
Glenn Robinson on Monday agreed to a one-year contract extension
that will keep the forward in the club through the 2004-2005 NBA
season.
</P>
<P>
The 6-foot-7 (2.0 m) five-year veteran had averaged 21.1 points
in 361 career games. He was the top overall pick in the 1994 draft
after earning national Player of the Year honours at Purdue.
</P>
<P>
In 361 career games, Robinson had averaged 21.1 points. He
ranks second in Bucks' history behind Kareem Abdul-Jabaar's 30.4
points per game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
