<HEADLINE> Regional First Aid Workshop Held in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regional First Aid Workshop Held in Myanmar
</P>
<P>
YANGON, December 7 (Xinhua) -- A regional first aid workshop,
being attending by delegates from South and Southeast Asia and the
Pacific, opened here Monday to share experience, exchange ideas
and review the success, gains, challenges and constraints
encountered in the field of first aid.
</P>
<P>
The five-day workshop, the fourth of its kind, is sponsored by
the Myanmar Red Cross Society (MRCS) and the International
Federation of the Red Cross and Red Crescent Society.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar Minister of Health Major-General Ket Sein told the
workshop that the MRCS has developed the first translated draft in
the Myanmar version of a resource manual for red cross and red
crescent volunteers -- "First Aid in the Community" -- initiated
at the Beijing Conference in May 1993.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar red cross volunteers were trained according to the
translated manual in the Myanmar language published after March
1996, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also said that Myanmar red cross volunteers have also
actively participated in the country's health programs since 1978
and have gained remarkable achievements in a national immunization
drive for five successive years. 
</P>
