<HEADLINE> Northeast China's Wheat Enters Hong Kong Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Heilongjiang Province, one of
the country's largest food production bases in northeast China
neighboring Russia, is to provide Hong Kong with 10,000 tons of
spring wheat.
</P>
<P>
The Heilongjiang Bureau for Land Reclamation recently signed a
contract on the spring wheat supply with the Hong Kong Lam Soon
Group, a leading food producer in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
After a series of sample tests, officials with Lam Soon said
that the spring wheat grown in Heilongjiang is of high quality and
can be used for food processing.
</P>
<P>
According to the contract, the Lam Soon Group will produce high-
quality flour using materials in Heilongjiang and processing
technologies in Hong Kong, and export the products to south Asian
countries.
</P>
<P>
Land reclamation in Heilongjiang started soon after the
founding of new China in 1949, and now the province has more than
100 large state-owned farms, which produce over five billion
kilograms of agricultural products each year. 
</P>
