<HEADLINE> Normal University in Guangzhou Trains Teachers for Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Over the past 15 years, South
China Normal University in this capital of Guangdong Province has
trained over 2,400 primary and middle school teachers for Macao,
74 percent of the region's total.
</P>
<P>
The university started its educational programs with
cooperation of the Macao education department and the Chinese
Education Association of Macao in 1985. The first group of 166
primary and middle school teachers in Macao received training
through correspondence courses.
</P>
<P>
To date, some 2,415 Macao teachers have received higher
education in a variety of fields including education and Chinese
literature. Some 105 Macao teachers have received post-graduate
education in various departments in the university. 
