<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Europe's Stock Markets End In Mixed Mode </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 6 (Xinhua) - Europe's major markets ended in a
mixed mode Monday as weak pharmaceutical stocks dragged down
London market, while buoyant telecom and tech shares boosted
Frankfurt and Paris higher.
</P>
<P>
London's benchmark FTSE 100 finished down 0.7 percent, or 48.2
points, at 6694.00 as slumping drug stocks erased the impact of
gains in the telecom sector.
</P>
<P>
Drug shares, which account for 12 percent of the FTSE 100's
overall value, dropped sharply as investors braced for a difficult
environment for the sector in the year ahead.
</P>
<P>
Glaxo Wellcome slumped 2.7 percent to 1826 pence, while rival
SmithKline Beecham tumbled 6.9 percent. AstraZeneca shed 7.3
percent, making it the sector's leading decliner.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, the electronically traded Xetra Dax gave up an
early assault on a new lifetime high to end 23.02 points higher at
6142.19.
</P>
<P>
Paris' CAC 40 advanced just over three quarters of a percent to
5509.97, topping it previous record of 5470.64 set last Friday.
</P>
</TEXT>
