<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks End Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, December 6 (Xinhua) - - Wall Street stocks ended
mixed Monday with the blue chip index falling while the technology
index rising.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed down 61.17 at 11,225.
01, cutting its big gain of 247.12 points Friday.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were mixed. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500
index fell 9.97 at 1,423.33 but the technology heavy Nasdaq
composite index rose 25.38 at 3,546.01, surpassing the record
closing high of 3,520.63 points set last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Dow index fell as investors sold stocks to take profits
from the strong rising in the previous session. The decline of
Coca-Cola's shares also help to drag the index lower.
</P>
<P>
Cock's shares slumped after the company announced that its
chairman and chief executive Douglas Ivester will step down in
April, next year.
</P>
<P>
But the Nasdaq index rose sharply as investors continued to
pour money into technology stocks after AT&AMP;T confirmed its plan to
spin off wireless operations as a separate affiliated company and
agreed to grand more companies access to its cable TV lines to
deliver high-speed Internet services as well.
</P>
<P>
Rising of the Red Hat's shares also lifted the Nasdaq index
higher. Red Hat, a leading seller of the Linux operating system,
rose sharply after Dell Computer agreed to install Linux on its
PowerEdge servers.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index fell 5.07 at 641.66 and the American Stock
Exchange index fell 5.43 at 829.82. But the Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies rose 1.17 at 465.75.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 7-to-4 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,966 down, 1,132 up and 483
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 906.57 million shares from 984.63
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
