<HEADLINE> Chinese Bank Pledges 100 Million Yuan Loan to Northwest Normal University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The Gansu Branch of
Construction Bank of China has pledged a 100-million yuan (12
million U.S. dollars) loan to Northwest Normal University in
Lanzhou, capital of Gansu Province, to improve its education
facilities.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhao Jinbao, dean of the university, the loan will
be used in the next three years mainly for construction of major
school buildings, renovation of key experimental labs and
application and development of new technology.
</P>
<P>
Major projects, such as the renovation and expansion of
Dunhuang Art School, construction of dormitories for foreign
students and graduates will start next year, he added.
</P>
<P>
The bank has been aiding the school for years with annual loans,
with priority given to its infrastructure construction.
</P>
<P>
One of the oldest normal universities in China, Northwest
Normal University has seven colleges and 16 departments. It is one
of the most comprehensive universities in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
