<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nicaragua Ready to Sue Honduras in The Hague </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Nicaraguan President Arnoldo
Aleman said Monday that his government is ready to sue Honduras in
the World Justice Court of The Hague.
</P>
<P>
Aleman told the press that Nicaragua made the decision to
safeguard the national sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the Nicaraguan leader dismissed the
possibility of using forces along borders with Honduras.
</P>
<P>
Tensions between Nicaragua and Honduras have been escalating
over the Honduras-Colombia maritime treaty which grants Honduras
and Colombia 130,000 square kilometers of Atlantic waters
historically claimed by Nicaragua.
</P>
<P>
Honduras since last Friday has sought foreign observers' help
to avoid a military showdown with Nicaragua as the two countries
continued claiming an area of Atlantic waters rich in fishing and
potential oil and natural gas resources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
